						               													<description>A solo soccer storytelling game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Experience the last minutes of the last match of a grueling soccer campaign, the glory or the heartbreak of an all-or-nothing result.  Ten minutes plus stoppage time remain.  All still to play for.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is the 80th minute . . .&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play you will need:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     10 to 20 minutes&amp;#10;     two 6-sided dice&amp;#10;     a standard 52 card deck&amp;#10;     a 20-sided die (or pen and paper)&amp;#10;     some way to narrate the events as they unfold on the pitch&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flip a card representing a minute of time and roll to see if your team has the grit to weather the late pressure, if the referee is going to add more time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Narrate the play on the field (for a radio, blog, or newspaper audience) based on prompts tied to each card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the last card is discarded before a goal is conceded, your team wins the title (or avoids relegation, or qualifies for the World Cup)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
